reviewText: I don't normally like movies of this genre but being a huge fan of Roger Daltrey I gave it a try and was very surprised by it.  The story is rather typical but the characters are extremely likable and the music is very good,especially the junk yard song/video.

It doesn't get any better than Mr. Chesney Hawkes in the underrated, under appreciated, Buddy's SOng.  His performance is riveting as well as the soundtrack which  he wrote the songs too.
All in all, this movie is worth the $92 just to see Chesney's face on the big screen, the man is a god!
